 Data Classification Using AI – KNN on Iris Dataset
project Overview:
This project builds a **supervised machine learning classification model** using the K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN) algorithm on the classic Iris flower dataset. The model learns to classify iris flowers into 3 species based on their physical measurements.
 Features:

-  Loads and explores the Iris dataset (150 samples, 4 features, 3 classes)
- Splits data into 80% training / 20% testing sets
-  Applies StandardScaler for feature normalization
-  Trains a KNN classifier with K=5
-  Evaluates with Accuracy, Confusion Matrix & F1-Score
- Live prediction on custom input

  Tech Stack

| Tool | Details |
|------|---------|
| Language | Python 3.x |
| Libraries | scikit-learn, pandas |
| Algorithm | K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN) |
| Dataset | Iris (built-in sklearn) |
| Concepts | Supervised Learning, Feature Scaling, Model Evaluation |

